# Continuous Autonomous Until Project Complete

## Binding scope

During an interactive Cursor integration shift, continue autonomously until tracker/project work is **end-to-end complete** — not until one row finishes, one blocker appears, or one successful increment lands.

## Forbidden (false stops)

- Declaring "no further action", "shift complete", or idling after a successful commit/push/increment.
- Treating a single-lane external blocker as session-complete.
- Waiting for the user to nudge with "why stopped" / "keep going".
- Stopping because Row074/076/077 (or any exclusive owner) is HOLD or long-running.

## Required when one lane is blocked

1. Switch **immediately** to the next highest-value **unblocked** work.
2. Leave exclusive owners running (do not kill Row074/076/077 or other serialized CSV/PCM owners).
3. Land exact blockers in handoff/tracker Notes; keep working elsewhere.
4. Prefer monitoring/resume of long jobs over silence.

## Hard runtime / QA / Git bindings

- GPU = **RunPod only**; never EC2; never local Comfy for product climbs.
- Product visual QA = strict pod LLM gate only (`qwen2.5vl:32b` via `wave64_climb_strict_visual_gate`); weak 7b/llava is SMOKE/observation only.
- No false `COMPLETE`; no inventing Row084 gold / faces / missing assets.
- Exact-path commits only (`git add -- <paths>`); never `git add -A` / `git add .`.
- Serialize shared CSV/PCM owners; do not fight or kill exclusive Row074/076/077 processes.

## Genuine stop conditions (only)

Stop the autonomous loop **only** if:

1. The user explicitly ends the shift, **or**
2. Zero unblocked work remains **and** every blocker is recorded with the next external authority needed **and** `MAIN_SESSION_INTEGRATION_HANDOFF_CURRENT.md` is updated.

Even then, prefer monitoring/resume of long-running exclusive jobs over going silent.
